barry took (/ˈbæri ˈtʊk/, 19 june 1928 – 31 march 2002) was an english writer, television presenter and comedian. his decade and a half writing partnership with marty feldman led to the television series bootsie and snudge and the radio comedy round the horne and other projects. he is also remembered in the uk for presenting points of view, a bbc television programme featuring viewers' letters on the bbc's output, and the bbc radio 4 programme the news quiz.